 the original French text. The editors also place the Livre de paix in historical context, provide a brief biography of Pizan, and offer insight into the translation process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh  aAristotle.  aChristine de Pizan.  aFrance.  aJohn the Fearless.  aLivre de paix.  aLouis of Guyenne.  aSaint-Denys.  acivil unrest.  acorruption.  apolitical and social influence.1 aGreen, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Karen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMews, Constant J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMews, Constant J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPinder, Janice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinder, Janice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVan Hemelryck, Tania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271056562423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271056562/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK